summary: I feel like tony stark’s line “and now there’s that guy” when thor shows up on the jet in avengers 1 is Extremely Underrated....
body: I feel like tony stark’s line “and now there’s that guy” when thor shows up on the jet in avengers 1 is Extremely Underrated. like, his date night with pepper gets interrupted by coulson, who drags him into this fucking magical shit show with a space cube nightlight, a norse god with fucking antlers and a glow stick of destiny, an angry man who turns big and green, and a defrosted super-soldier from the 1940s. and of course - Of Fucking Course - now there’s That Guy with an overcompensating hammer who can summon lightning. because why the fuck not?

summary: Happy Pride Month! How about Deadpool with Spider-Man?
question: Happy Pride Month! How about Deadpool with Spider-Man?
answer:
Wade was roughly fifteen years older than Peter, and scarred as all hell, and sure, he has muscles, but it hardly made up for his face and skin and anxiety. 

So when Peter comes over saying if he has to deal with his stupid roomates and awful cup ramen for one more second he’s going to kill someone, he doesn’t think much of it. Wade didn’t go to college, but it sure seems stressful. 

He’s completely unprepared for Peter pushing him against the wall and kissing him, but he had absolutely no complaints.
